docs.lead_paragraph: CORDOVA, Alaska, Jan. 27. -- A phenomenal change in the course of the Japan current, which brings it closer to the Alaskan coast, was reported here to-day by Capt. J.C. Hunter of the steamer Northwestern and Capt. P.A. Obert of the steamer Edith, arriving from Seattle. Capt. Hunter said the Northwestern was set fifty miles eastward ahead of the log, running from Cape Flattery to Cape St. Elias.

headline.main: JAPAN STREAM HUGS ALASKA.; Change in Current Makes the Territory Warmer.
